        public LineAnalyzer.LineType checkFormat​(java.lang.String line,
                                         LineFormatFactory lfFactory)
                                  throws UnsupportedSyntaxException
        Check if the line is in the right format for variable declaration. If it's legal return the line type (as enum).
        Parameters:
        line - The source file line of code the program is currently processing.
        lfFactory - A instance of LineFormatFactroy Class.
        Returns:
        The type of the given line (Method declaration, variable declaration etc)
        Throws:
        UnsupportedSyntaxException - Stands for an unsupported code line syntax.
